{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}} {{Use British English|date=August 2015}} :''For others named William Agnew, see the [[William Agnew (disambiguation)|William Agnew]] navigation page'' {{Infobox football biography | name = Billy Agnew | image = | caption = | fullname = William Agnew<ref name="kent"/> | birth_date = {{birth date|1898|01|09|df=y}}<ref name="kent"/> | birth_place = [[Pollokshaws]], Scotland<ref name="kent"/> | death_date = <!--{{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|1898|01|09|df=y}}--> | death_place = | height = | position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = [[Pollok F.C.|Pollok]] | years1 = | clubs1 = [[Ayr United F.C.|Ayr United]]| caps1 = | goals1 = | years2 = | clubs2 = [[Falkirk F.C.|Falkirk]]| caps2 = | goals2 = | years3 = 1921–1923| clubs3 = [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]]| caps3 = 42| goals3 = 6 | years4 = 1923–1925| clubs4 = [[Arthurlie F.C.|Arthurlie]]| caps4 = | goals4 = | years5 = 1925–1927| clubs5 = [[Luton Town F.C.|Luton Town]]| caps5 = 35| goals5 = 8 | totalcaps = 77+| totalgoals = 14+ }}
'''William Agnew''' (9 January 1898 – ?) was a [[Scottish people|Scottish]] [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Pollok F.C.|Pollok]], [[Ayr United F.C.|Ayr United]], [[Falkirk F.C.|Falkirk]], [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]], [[Arthurlie F.C.|Arthurlie]], and [[Luton Town F.C.|Luton Town]].
==Playing career== Agnew played for [[Pollok F.C.|Pollok]], [[Ayr United F.C.|Ayr United]] and [[Falkirk F.C.|Falkirk]], before moving down to England to sign with [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]] in September 1921.<ref name="kent">{{cite book|last=Kent|first=Jeff|title=Port Vale Personalities|publisher=Witan Books|page=4|year=1996|isbn=0-9529152-0-0|url=https://www.amazon.ca/Port-Vale-Personalities-Jeff-Kent/dp/0952915200}}</ref> He hit a total of five goals in 31 appearances in the [[1921–22 Port Vale F.C. season|1921–22]] season, and scored his first goal in the [[Football League Second Division|Second Division]] on 29 October, in a 1–0 win at [[South Shields F.C. (1889)|South Shields]].<ref name="kent"/> However, he was used more sparingly the [[1922–23 Port Vale F.C. season|next season]], and scored just one goal in 11 games.<ref name="kent"/> After undergoing [[cartilage]] operations in the spring of 1923 he was released from his contract at [[The Old Recreation Ground]].<ref name="kent"/> He moved on to [[Arthurlie F.C.|Arthurlie]] of the [[Scottish Football League Third Division|Scottish Third Division]], and then returned to [[the Football League]] to play for [[Luton Town F.C.|Luton Town]].<ref name="kent"/>
