'''Fedor Mikhailovich Dubiansky''' ({{lang-ru|Федор Михайлович Дубянский}}; 1760 &ndash; 4 August 1796) was a Russian [[amateur]] musician and the author of the romance "A rock-dove moans" ({{lang-ru|Стонет сизый голубочек..}})<ref>{{cite web|title=Федор Дубянский. Стонет сизый голубочек / Feodor Dubiansky. A rock-dove moans|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-sqWFezaCho|website=Youtube}}</ref> after the text of [[Ivan Dmitriev|Ivan Ivanovich Dmitriev]]. He drowned while crossing the [[Neva]] in 1796, aged 36.<ref name=Orfey>{{cite web|title=Дубянский Фёдор Михайлович|url=http://orfey.club/kompozitori/dubyanskiy-fyodor-mihaylovich/}}</ref>

