{{Infobox video game | title = Kitten Sanctuary | collapsible = | state = | image = | caption = | developer = [[Clockwork Pixels]] | publisher = | series = | engine = | platforms = [[iOS]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[Windows]], [[macOS]] | released = March 27, 2012 | genre = | modes = }}
'''''Kitten Sanctuary''''' is the first [[iOS]] game of British indie developer [[Clockwork Pixels]], and was released on March 27, 2012.
==Critical reception== The game has a [[Metacritic]] score of 85% based on 4 critic reviews.<ref>http://www.metacritic.com/game/ios/kitten-sanctuary</ref>
SlideToPlay wrote "Not every game needs to be about guns or swords, and Kitten Sanctuary is a great alternative to the violence that computer games are often associated with. "<ref>http://www.slidetoplay.com/review/kitten-sanctuary-review/</ref> [[TouchArcade]] wrote "Kitten Sanctuary is a very sweet game, but beyond that it's well-crafted, and the attention to detail shows. "<ref>http://toucharcade.com/2012/04/09/kitten-sanctuary-review/</ref> AppSpy said "While this is definitely aimed at younger players and lovers of all things kitten, the match three is fun and you definitely get your share of virtual pets. "<ref>http://www.appspy.com/review/5387/kitten-sanctuary-review</ref> 148Apps said "Kitten Sanctuary doesn't reinvent the cheese wheel here (sorry), but the game successfully blends classic genres in an unexpected way that kept me playing far longer than I anticipated. It's a solid pick-up for casual gamers and cat ladies alike. "<ref>http://www.148apps.com/reviews/kitten-sanctuary-review/</ref>
